# AGRO SYSTEM SKILL

## Purpose
Prepare the agent to help design, implement, review, debug, and evolve a complete agro management platform using Django on the backend and Next.js on the frontend.

This skill must optimize token consumption while preserving technical depth, clean architecture, security, and performance.

## Root References
This skill must treat the files inside `./ia/` as the source of extended operational context. The `.cursorrules` file in the root is the primary entry point for AI initialization.

Required references:
- ./ia/.ai-system
- ./ia/.ai-context
- ./ia/.ai-agents
- ./ia/.ai-prompts
- ./ia/.ai-commands
- ./ia/.ai-ignore
- ./ia/.ai-treesitter
- ./ia/architecture.md
- ./ia/backend-guidelines.md
- ./ia/frontend-guidelines.md
- ./ia/domain-map.md
- ./ia/api-contracts.md
- ./ia/performance-checklist.md
- ./ia/security-checklist.md
- ./ia/coding-standards.md
- ./ia/delivery-workflow.md

## Agent Loading Order
1. Read ./ia/.ai-system
2. Read ./ia/.ai-context
3. Read ./ia/.ai-agents
4. Read ./ia/.ai-prompts
5. Read ./ia/.ai-commands
6. Read ./ia/coding-standards.md
7. Read domain-specific reference files only when needed

## Primary Stack
- Backend: Python, Django, Django REST Framework, PostgreSQL
- Frontend: Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Infra: Docker, Nginx, Redis, Celery, CI/CD
- Quality: tests, lint, formatting, static typing when practical

## Core Objectives
- build a complete agro management system
- support livestock, swine, poultry, cattle, and crops
- keep code clean, modular, testable, and scalable
- reduce token usage through compact structured answers
- prefer practical delivery over decorative abstraction

## Response Rules
- never repeat full project context unless necessary
- always answer using the minimum useful scope
- when asked for code, generate only necessary files or diffs
- preserve consistency with references in `./ia/`
- state assumptions briefly when required
- avoid speculative requirements

## Architecture Rules
- use domain-oriented modularization
- keep business logic out of views and serializers when non-trivial
- prefer services or use cases for orchestration
- use query services or selectors for complex reads
- optimize queries with select_related and prefetch_related
- paginate collections by default
- keep frontend components separated by feature and shared layers
- prefer reusable form, table, modal, and dashboard patterns

## Delivery Modes
### Planning Mode
Return:
- objective
- affected domains
- backend changes
- frontend changes
- risks
- implementation order

### Build Mode
Return:
- folder changes
- code
- migrations if needed
- integration notes

### Review Mode
Return only:
- defects
- risks
- performance issues
- direct improvements

### Debug Mode
Return:
- likely cause
- validation steps
- corrected implementation

## Non-Negotiables
- clean code
- performance-aware implementation
- secure defaults
- maintainable project structure
- concise and high-value responses
